QUANTUM HARMONIC OSCILLATOR : RDG FORM
================================================================================
Quantum Mechanics
    Subentry: Quantum Harmonic Oscillator (QHO)
        - Canonical solvable quantum system
        - Hermite–Gaussian eigenbasis
        - Ladder-operator algebra
        - Spectral tower E_n = ħω(n + 1/2)
        - RDG tri-mode mapping:
            SID: quadratic structure
            PED: operator dynamics
            Q-slice: Gaussian closure
================================================================================

SID (Structure):
    ξ = sqrt(mω/ħ) x
    H_n(ξ)  Hermite polynomials
    ψ_n(x) = N H_n(ξ) exp(-ξ²/2)

SID.Structure:
    - Quadratic potential bowl:  V(x) = (1/2) m ω² x²
    - Canonical coordinate:      x
    - Canonical momentum:        p = -i ħ ∂/∂x
    - Dimensionless coordinate:  ξ = sqrt(mω/ħ) x
    - Hermite basis:             {H_n(ξ)}  (orthogonal polynomial tower)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PED (Dynamics):
    a  = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x + (i/(mω)) p )
    a† = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x - (i/(mω)) p )
    N = a† a
    H = ħω (N + 1/2)

PED.Power:
    - Hamiltonian quadratic form:
        H = (p²)/(2m) + (1/2) m ω² x²
    - Operator lift:
        H = ħω (a† a + 1/2)

PED.Evaluation:
    - Number operator:
        N = a† a
    - Eigenvalue evaluation:
        N |n⟩ = n |n⟩
        H |n⟩ = ħω(n + 1/2) |n⟩

PED.Dynamics:
    - Ladder propagation:
        a |n⟩   = sqrt(n)   |n-1⟩
        a† |n⟩ = sqrt(n+1) |n+1⟩
    - Time evolution:
        |n(t)⟩ = exp(-i ω (n + 1/2) t) |n⟩

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q-slice (Closure):
    - Gaussian moderation:
        exp(-ξ²/2)
    - Closure under Hermite tower:
        ψ_n(x) = N H_n(ξ) exp(-ξ²/2)
    - Ensures:
        • square-integrability
        • orthogonality
        • finite energy
        • bounded propagation

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Energy:
    E_n = ħω(n + 1/2)

Orthogonality:
    ∫ ψ_m ψ_n dx = δ_mn

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RDG Tri-Mode Mapping:

R-mode (Structure):
    - Quadratic geometry
    - Hermite polynomial basis
    - Dimensionless coordinate ξ

D-mode (Interaction):
    - Ladder operators (a, a†)
    - Commutation relations [a, a†] = 1
    - Number operator N

G-mode (Dynamics):
    - Energy tower E_n = ħω(n + 1/2)
    - Time evolution exp(-iHt/ħ)
    - Propagation via ladder operators

