QHO Hamiltonian
================================================================================

RDG.H_QHO  :=  ( H_SID , H_PED , H_Q )

    H_SID : structural quadratic form
        H_SID(x, p) = p²/(2m) + (1/2) m ω² x²

    H_PED : operator lift
        H_PED = ħω (N + 1/2)

    H_Q   : moderated spectral action
        H_Q ψ_n = ħω (n + 1/2) ψ_n
        with ψ_n(x) = N H_n(ξ) exp(-ξ²/2)

Q-slice.H (Moderated Hamiltonian):

    Basis:
        ψ_n(x) = N H_n(ξ) exp(-ξ²/2)

    Closure:
        H ψ_n(x) = E_n ψ_n(x)
        E_n = ħω (n + 1/2)

    Moderation:
        - Gaussian factor exp(-ξ²/2) ensures:
            • square-integrability
            • finite energy
            • bounded propagation
        - Hermite tower {H_n(ξ)} provides:
            • complete eigenbasis
            • orthogonality: ∫ ψ_m ψ_n dx = δ_mn

PED.H (Operator Hamiltonian):

    Ladder operators:
        a  = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x + (i/(mω)) p )
        a† = sqrt(mω/(2ħ)) ( x - (i/(mω)) p )

    Number operator:
        N = a† a

    Operator lift:
        H_PED = ħω (N + 1/2)

    Spectral action:
        H_PED |n⟩ = ħω (n + 1/2) |n⟩

SID.H (Structural Hamiltonian):

    Coordinates:
        x  : canonical position
        p  : canonical momentum = -i ħ ∂/∂x

    Quadratic potential:
        V(x) = (1/2) m ω² x²

    Dimensionless coordinate:
        ξ = sqrt(mω/ħ) x

    Structural Hamiltonian (coordinate form):
        H_SID(x, p) = p²/(2m) + (1/2) m ω² x²

